text: Nizhneye Babalarovo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Yakshimbetovsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 230 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 45 km from Yermolayevo, 18 km from Yakshimbetovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Nizhneye Babalarovo
